001    package tv.freewheel.ad.interfaces;
002    
003    import java.util.HashMap;
004    
005    /**
006     * IEvent is the value object for carrying out event info:
007     */
008    public interface IEvent {
009    
010            /**
011             * Get the type of this event.
012             *
013             * @return type string, can be one of:
014             *              <br>IConstants.EVENT_REQUEST_COMPLETE
015             *              <br>IConstants.EVENT_REQUEST_CONTENT_VIDEO_PAUSE
016             *              <br>IConstants.EVENT_REQUEST_CONTENT_VIDEO_RESUME
017             *              <br>IConstants.EVENT_SLOT_ENDED
018             *              <br>IConstants.EVENT_SLOT_STARTED
019             *              <br>IConstants.EVENT_AD_*
020             */
021            public String getType();
022            
023            /**
024             * Get the data information of this event.
025             *
026             * @return data as an {@code HashMap<String, Object>} Object
027             * 
028             * <p>
029             * Note: the key of the data as following:
030             *              <br>
031             *              <br>IConstants.INFO_KEY_MESSAGE :all event will contain this
032             *              <br>IConstants.INFO_KEY_CUSTOM_ID :IConstants.EVENT_SLOT_ENDED/IConstants.EVENT_SLOT_STARTED will contain this
033             *              <br>IConstants.INFO_KEY_ADINSTANCE : IConstants.EVENT_AD_* will contain this
034             */
035            public HashMap<String, Object> getData();
036    }
